This AGREEMENT is made and entered into on this 12th day of July, 2023, by and between Green Valley Farms, a producer of agricultural products ("GVF"), Natural Foods Cooperative, a retail food cooperative ("NFC"), and Organic Distribution Inc., a logistics service provider ("ODI") (collectively referred to as the "Parties").

WHEREAS, Green Valley Farms is engaged in the business of agricultural production and seeks to expand its distribution channels;

WHEREAS, Natural Foods Cooperative operates a network of food retail establishments serving health-conscious consumers;

WHEREAS, Organic Distribution Inc. provides logistics and distribution services for agricultural products;

WHEREAS, the Parties wish to establish a collaborative relationship for the distribution of agricultural products to better serve their respective business interests;

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises and covenants contained herein, the Parties agree as follows:

1. PURPOSE
The purpose of this Agreement is to establish a framework for collaboration among the Parties for the distribution of agricultural products from Green Valley Farms to Natural Foods Cooperative's retail locations through Organic Distribution Inc.'s logistics network.

2. ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
2.1 Green Valley Farms shall be responsible for producing and preparing agricultural products for distribution.
2.2 Organic Distribution Inc. shall coordinate and execute the transportation and delivery of products.
2.3 Natural Foods Cooperative shall receive and retail the products through its network of stores.

3. QUALITY STANDARDS
The Parties agree to maintain appropriate quality standards in their respective operations to ensure the delivery of high-quality products to end consumers.
